s\" data, the delayed operations between `cartservice` and `redis` and the significant rise in latency here point towards these interactions as the potential root cause of the delays further propagating through `cartservice`.\n\n### JSON Output\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"rrt_max\", \"cartservice->redis\", \"checkoutservice->paymentservice\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Significant delay in cartservice's HGET operation with redis across multiple nodes, approximately 6x normal duration.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Delays in downstream operations of checkoutservice including payment charging and email sending, caused by upstream delays.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Conclusion**: The hypothesis that delays between `cartservice` and `redis` interaction caused the system fault during the specified time is supported. The root bottleneck stems from these delays, which propagates through the system, especially affecting `checkoutservice` operations.", "current_hypothesis": "'adservice-2' is the root cause due to pod_cpu_usage and pod_processes spikes, impacting node_cpu_usage_rate on 'aiops-k8s-08'."}
